<paragraph blockId="10.[163,780,199,435]" pageId="10">
<emphasis box="[163,292,199,220]" italics="true" pageId="10">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is unique in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okada" authorityYear="1971" box="[679,779,199,220]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shirozui">
<emphasis box="[679,779,199,220]" italics="true" pageId="10">shirozui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in having the mesoscutum and scutellum predominantly yellow, laterally with brownish longitudinal strips on mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[593,711,291,313]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[163,241,1019,1041]" captionTargetBox="[170,775,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure-647@8.[167,775,195,979]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Habitus ofholotypes.A,B.Stegana (Steganina) alianya sp. nov.; C, D. Stegana (Steganina) diodonta sp. nov.; E, F. Stegana (Steganina) zebromyia sp. nov.; G, H. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov." pageId="10">Fig. 4C, D</figureCitation>
), and surstylus with two prensisetae submedially (
<figureCitation box="[659,765,321,343]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[145,223,1763,1785]" captionTargetBox="[306,1266,1082,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-80@9.[303,1266,1078,1724]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Stegana (Steganina) diodonta sp. nov.A.epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres (pm), aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="10">Fig.6A, B</figureCitation>
). In other species of this group, the mesoscutum is usually dark brown to black, laterally with yellow longitudinal strips (
<figureCitation box="[389,502,413,435]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[163,241,1019,1041]" captionTargetBox="[170,775,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure-647@8.[167,775,195,979]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Habitus ofholotypes.A,B.Stegana (Steganina) alianya sp. nov.; C, D. Stegana (Steganina) diodonta sp. nov.; E, F. Stegana (Steganina) zebromyia sp. nov.; G, H. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov." pageId="10">Fig. 4A, G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
