<paragraph blockId="10.[163,303,871,894]" box="[163,303,871,894]" pageId="10">
<emphasis box="[163,303,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="10">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[163,779,911,994]" pageId="10">
<emphasis box="[163,446,911,932]" italics="true" pageId="10">Male and female. Head:</emphasis>
Frons yellow above, brown below. First flagellomere yellow, black on distal third. Clypeus brownish. Palpus yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[827,1443,198,435]" pageId="10">
<emphasis box="[827,1164,198,220]" italics="true" pageId="10">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1145,198,220]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[145,223,1763,1785]" captionTargetBox="[306,1266,1082,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-80@9.[303,1266,1078,1724]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Stegana (Steganina) diodonta sp. nov.A.epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres (pm), aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="10">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Epandrium slightly broadened on posterior margins, more than half as wide as long, ventrally slightly protruded. Cercus lacking pubescence. Paramere with two sensilla. Opening of aedeagus nearly oblong in ventral view, lateral parts lacking serrated processes. Gonopods posteromedially concave in ventral view, dorsomedially protruded in lateral view.
</paragraph>
